"content": "The mechanism of transport is much more elaborate in multicellular higher plants. The process of diffusion cannot meet the requirements of transport in higher plants as it is a slow process. In such plants, there are special channels called xylem and phloem, which comprises conducting tissues or vascular tissues\n\nHence, in higher plants, transport of materials like water, minerals and sugar takes place through xylem and phloem. :\n\nMovement of water and minerals takes place from the roots to other plant parts through the stem. Upward movement of water and minerals occurs through channels, called xylem elements, which are present in roots, stem and leaves of plants\n\nMovement of food material, synthesised in the leaves, occur in soluble form through another channel, called phloem. It transports the food from the leaves to all other parts of the plant's body",
