"explanation": "Key points:\n• Temperature is associated with Influences the external appearance and body functions of plants and animals.\n• Air is associated with Provides oxygen to animals and carbon dioxide to plants; acts as a medium of pollen and seed dispersal.\n• Water is associated with Helps the plants to carry out photosynthesis; constitutes a major part in a living organism&#x27;s body.\n• Inorganic substances such as carbon dioxide, oxygen, nitrogen, water.\n• Organic compounds, such as proteins, carbohydrates and fats.\n• Climatic factors, these are of two types—.\n• (a) atmospheric factors (such as temperature, light, humidity, wind, rainfall).\n• (b) edaphic factors (pertaining to soil).\n• Humans are omnivores since they consume both plant material as well as animals.\n• Cockroach and ox are also omnivores.\n• Acts as a medium of pollen and seed dispersal. Water Helps the plants to carry out photosynthesis.\n• Constitutes a major part in a living organism&#x27.\n• Removal of even a single population from the ecosystem can upset the whole ecological balance.\n• Depending upon their mode of nutrition, the biotic component of an ecosystem is primarily made up of three kinds of organisms - autotrophs, heterotrophs and decomposers.\n• Apart from the requirement of water for all living organisms, water is required for.\n• Provides water and minerals to the plants.\n• Weathering is brought about by many agents — physical (temperature, rain, wind, frost) and biological (by living organisms — plants, animals and microbes).\n• Climatic factors, such as light, temperature, rainfall and humidity.\n\nDefinitions:\n• Temperature — associated with Influences the external appearance and body functions of plants and animals\n• Water — associated with Helps the plants to carry out photosynthesis; constitutes a major part in a living organism&#x27;s body\n• Climatic factors, these — of two types—\n• Humans — omnivores since they consume both plant material as well as animals\n• Cockroach and ox — also omnivores"
