"subtopic": "11. I. Tick (✓) the correct choice",
"content": "1. Chemical control in organisms is brought about by\n\n(a) Enzymes (b) Neurons (c) Hormones (d) All of these\n\n(a) Thyroid (b) Pituitary (c) Pancreas (d) Adrenal\n\n3. The hormone thyroxine is secreted by\n\n(a) Pituitary gland (b) Adrenal gland (c) Thyroid gland (d) Pancreas\n\n5. A gland that secretes both the enzyme and the hormone is\n\n(a) Liver (b) Pituitary (c) Thyroid (d) Pancreas\n\n6. The secretion of milk in human females is stimulated by the hormone (a) Prolactin (b) Thyroxine (c) Growth hormone (d) TSH",
"explanation": "Key points:\n• Hormones are chemical substances secreted by endocrine glands.\n• Chemical coordination in living beings is brought about by chemical substances called hormones.\n\nDefinitions:\n• Hormones — chemical substances secreted by endocrine glands\n• Chemical coordination in living beings — brought about by chemical substances called hormones"
